what plant family are the hen and biddies in hens and chicks are in the family crassulaceae their genus and species are sempervivum tectorum they are considered succulents and generally do well with the same sort of soil and care that you would give to cacti or aloe plants a somewhat sandy potting soil works well you can get potting soil specifically for cacti and succulents at most garden stores a high nitrogen high first number fertilizer and only occasional watering usually work nicely Hen and chicks Houseleek Crassulaceae Houseplant Pachypodium Pachypodium bicolor Carnivorous plant Pachypodium habitats Habitats of Pachypodium of Southern Continental Africa and Madagascar Bonsai Pachypodium baronii Pachypodium key to species Weed control Echinopsis Echeveria San Pedro cactus Pachypodium brevicaule Chicken Earthworm Invalid species and varieties of Pachypodium Soil Agriculture History of the genus Pachypodium Aloe Morphology of Pachypodium Nitrogen fixation Begonia Hippeastrum Desert Flowering plant Sewage treatment Bacteria Pine Lanzarote Comfrey Euphorbiaceae Sorghum Sedum Soil life Cycad Capercaillie Hemp Eutrophication Common bean Apricot Spurge Irrigation Coffee Fertilizer Gardening Citrus Ecology Agave Alfalfa Gooseberry Fruit tree propagation Soil pH Lupin Alder Egg (food) Areole Tillandsia Fabaceae Vegetation Leaf Larger context to habitats of Pachypodium Organic farming Nutrient Horsetail Garden Strawberry Mammillaria Caatinga Lawn Wisteria Oenothera Banksia Fat Hen Iris (plant) Invasive plants Plant Compost Erosion Tree Hydroponics Green manure Heath (habitat) Sustainable agriculture Garden Pea Plant breeding Photosynthesis Desertification Pitcher plant Town gas Jade plant Hamster Organic gardening Environmental concerns with electricity generation 